$ Access: DoCmd.ApplyFilter

code {
→ Microsoft/Office/Access/Object-Model/DoCmd/openTable[doCmd.openTable]   "contracts"
docmd.applyFilter "contracts", "contract_nr = '81845'"
code }

?If the first argument is omitted, the filter is applied to the active object that has the focus:
code {
docmd.applyFilter , "contract_nr = '81845'"
code }

sa:
  → Microsoft/Office/Access/Object-Model/DoCmd/setFilter[`DoCmd.SetFilter`] and
 `DoCmd.ShowAllRecords`.

  After applying a filter, the records can be ordered (sorted) with → Microsoft/Office/Access/Object-Model/DoCmd/setOrderBy/[`DoCmd.SetOrderBy`].

  → Microsoft/Office/Access/Object-Model/DoCmd/findRecord[`DoCmd.findRecord`]

  The → Microsoft/Office/Access/Object-Model/DoCmd[`DoCmd` object]
